Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.02,0:00:14.99,Ore_Flashback,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to force \Nyourself to attend anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.45,0:00:32.16,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the joint event is a week away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.16,0:00:34.68,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,So I went to check on the meeting, \Nbut it was already over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.45,0:00:39.04,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I was on my way home, too, when I found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.84,0:00:40.62,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.31,0:00:44.77,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the car you drive?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.53,0:00:47.47,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like the \None you had in summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.47,0:00:49.77,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that was a rental.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.38,0:00:52.17,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,This baby's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.92,0:00:54.94,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Hikigaya...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.46,0:00:58.38,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Mind if we make a little stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.33,0:01:06.50,Show_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(235,1)}My Teen\NRomantic\NComedy\N{\c&H8D39E0&}SNAFU\N{\c&HDCA02E&}TOO!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.96,0:02:49.00,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:59.19,bridge_02:57,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Mihama Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:59.19,wont_lose_02:57,Text,0000,0000,0000,,I\Nwon't\Nlose!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.19,0:03:01.45,4month_02:59,Text,0000,0000,0000,,I love Yuu-kun-chan!\N4 month anniversary!!\NWe'll be together forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.28,0:03:09.20,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Hikigaya!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.42,0:03:23.39,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You look kinda cool like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.39,0:03:25.34,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm trying to look cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:31.53,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,So, how are things going?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.98,0:03:33.57,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's looking pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.29,0:03:35.56,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,What's looking bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.56,0:03:38.57,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to say exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.14,0:03:41.40,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Well, try telling me anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.70,0:03:42.91,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.63,0:03:45.54,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.19,0:03:50.17,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess time is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.73,0:03:54.54,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see how we can turn this \Nsituation around in a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.24,0:03:58.84,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Tamanawa and Isshiki are both scared
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:01.42,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,to think of this thing \Nfailing because of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:05.79,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,So, to distribute the responsibility, \Nthey ask for others' opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.18,0:04:07.22,blackboard_11:20,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Christmas Event\N-Orchestra\N-Band\N-Jazz concert\N-Choir\N-Dance\N-Play\N-Gospel\N-Musical\N-Dramatic reading
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.79,0:04:07.22,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,and try to implement those.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.57,0:04:10.98,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,And the result is this \Nplateau we're stuck on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.36,0:04:13.19,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,We were wrong not to decide
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.21,0:04:18.41,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,who's on top, and who should \Nbear the responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.15,0:04:21.46,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.30,0:04:25.74,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You have a good eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.35,0:04:29.54,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You're very good at reading \Npeople's mental states.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.50,0:04:31.46,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.46,0:04:32.38,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:35.25,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.49,0:04:40.28,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,One's mental state and the emotions \Nthey feel aren't always equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.21,0:04:45.26,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they sometimes reach conclusions \Nthat seem completely illogical.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.92,0:04:48.90,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Yukinoshita, Yuigahama, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.24,0:04:50.90,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,all give wrong answers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.28,0:04:55.02,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, they have nothing to \Ndo with this, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.22,0:04:59.14,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,They're the ones I was asking \Nyou about in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:06.49,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,But, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:09.11,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,In essence, they're both the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:11.49,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Both problems have the same root.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.21,0:05:13.41,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,It's in the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.63,0:05:18.33,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not something you can \Nunderstand by thinking, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.03,0:05:21.39,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.09,0:05:24.04,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Then think harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:26.68,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,If you can only think in terms of \Ncalculations, then calculate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:28.39,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Lay out all the answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:30.51,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and knock them out one by one \Nvia process of elimination.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.85,0:05:33.72,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,What's left, in the end, is your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.09,0:05:39.81,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it's not something you \Ncan really understand, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.13,0:05:44.39,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Then either you calculated wrong, \Nor you missed something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.39,0:05:46.32,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You just have to calculate \Nit all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.24,0:05:48.81,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You're nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.81,0:05:50.25,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.25,0:05:53.58,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,If emotions could be calculated, \Nthey'd have been digitized by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.33,0:05:56.74,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,The answer left behind because \Nyou couldn't calculate it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.23,0:05:59.52,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,is what you call "human emotion."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.38,0:06:03.89,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I say that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.89,0:06:07.94,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's probably because I keep \Nmiscalculating that I can't get married...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.28,0:06:11.37,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Just the other day, my friend got married...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.37,0:06:14.45,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's because the guys \Nyou know have lousy taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.45,0:06:15.21,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.80,0:06:19.56,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd been born ten years earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:21.96,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd met her ten years earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.96,0:06:25.11,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I probably would've fallen \Nmadly in love with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.63,0:06:27.60,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Not that there's any point \Nin hypothesizing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.60,0:06:29.88,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Where'd that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.88,0:06:31.79,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,N-Never mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.79,0:06:35.37,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't call it thanking you, \Nbut I'll give you a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.70,0:06:42.88,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,When you think, don't pinpoint \Nthe wrong thing to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.17,0:06:44.13,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,For example...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.66,0:06:46.86,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you're helping \NIsshiki individually,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.86,0:06:49.28,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,and not as part of the Service Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.95,0:06:51.55,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Try thinking about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.88,0:06:53.74,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,For the Service Club's sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.74,0:06:55.22,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,or in other words, for Yukinoshita's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.71,0:06:58.30,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,It's plain to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.73,0:07:01.85,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinoshita came to report \Nto me after the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.88,0:07:06.68,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,She won't talk about herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.68,0:07:09.45,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,but just watching her, \NI thought it might be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.08,0:07:11.72,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Does that go for you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.17,0:07:14.83,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... er... I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:18.33,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,If you had the same thing in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:21.27,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,you might arrive at the idea of distancing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:24.34,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,yourself from them so \Nyou wouldn't hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.62,0:07:26.15,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Hypothetically, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.52,0:07:27.98,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.41,0:07:30.03,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Hypothetically, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.43,0:07:32.97,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not what you need to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.31,0:07:36.41,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, what you should \Nthink about is why you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.41,0:07:37.64,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,don't want to hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.15,0:07:40.51,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,And that answer will come \Nto you immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.83,0:07:44.98,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to hurt them because \Nthey're important to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.79,0:07:48.36,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, Hikigaya...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.21,0:07:51.49,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible not to hurt someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.23,0:07:57.03,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Humans unconsciously hurt \Nothers simply by existing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.34,0:08:00.83,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Whether you're alive or dead, \Nyou keep hurting people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:03.31,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Getting involved will hurt them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.31,0:08:06.53,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,but trying not to get involved \Nmight hurt them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.72,0:08:09.84,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,But if it's someone you don't care about,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.84,0:08:11.72,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,you won't notice you've hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.14,0:08:13.80,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,What's important is your awareness of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.19,0:08:15.97,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you care about them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.97,0:08:17.95,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,that you feel like you've hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.86,0:08:21.45,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Caring about someone means
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:24.44,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,being resolved to the fact \Nthat you'll hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:30.82,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,That's your hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:34.07,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,The more people care for each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.56,0:08:36.36,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,the farther out of reach certain things get.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.87,0:08:39.84,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not something to be sad about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.23,0:08:42.58,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's probably \Nsomething to be proud of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.22,0:08:45.29,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that kinda hard to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.29,0:08:47.21,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, it's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.84,0:08:50.59,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But you can do it. I could, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:57.22,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little arrogant to say someone \Nelse can do it just because you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.56,0:08:59.51,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,You're so unlovable!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.73,0:09:02.80,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.40,0:09:04.63,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.24,0:09:08.23,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,It probably doesn't have to be you, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.03,0:09:10.48,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Someday,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.88,0:09:13.22,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinoshita might change on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:17.39,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Someone might show up \Nwho can understand her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.79,0:09:20.99,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Someone might get inside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.63,0:09:24.25,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,The same can be said for Yuigahama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.16,0:09:28.13,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Someday?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:33.74,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,For you kids, right now \Nfeels like everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:35.92,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not true at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:38.29,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,At some point, everything will balance out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.76,0:09:41.01,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,That's how the world is made.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.57,0:09:43.52,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.95,0:09:46.39,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,think it'd be nice if it could be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.95,0:09:50.78,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hoping you and Yuigahama \Ncan get inside Yukinoshita.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.08,0:09:53.28,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:55.67,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know what to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.48,0:09:59.54,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Right now isn't everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:01.93,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,but there are things you can only do now,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.36,0:10:04.04,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,and things you can only have here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.51,0:10:07.04,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Hikigaya. Now is the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:12.80,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Think. Agonize. Struggle. Worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.32,0:10:15.05,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, it's not the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.29,0:10:25.35,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.90,0:10:28.98,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Just because you suffered doesn't \Nmake it the real thing, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.31,0:10:32.08,Ore_Main,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, you're so unlovable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.71,0:10:53.66,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,The biggest immediate obstacle is, \Nobviously, the joint Christmas event.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.99,0:10:58.39,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,The problem with Isshiki \NIroha is attached to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.13,0:11:00.84,employment_10:57,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(735,723)}Employment consultations on the rise
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.45,0:11:00.31,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}And the situation with Tsurumi \NRumi ties into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.31,0:11:03.05,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the ideal solution \Nto all three problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.74,headline_11:00,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Diversifying Communication
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.74,subheadline_11:00,Text,0000,0000,0000,,The uses and shortcomings of modern tools
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.74,subheadline_11:00 - Copy,Text,0000,0000,0000,,An\NUnexpected\NCrisis...?\NThe\NPitfalls\NLurking\Nin\NConvenience
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.74,subheadlineL_11:00,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Proactively\Nstart a\Ndialogue\Nnow and\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.74,subheadlinebot_11:00,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Requesting the Cooperation of Students
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.74,0:11:04.83,Dangers_11:02,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(631,1)}Dangers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:05.59,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't turn that situation around alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.83,0:11:07.04,ccoperation_11:04,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(543,1)}Cooperation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.59,0:11:06.77,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Should I ask someone for help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.77,0:11:08.85,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I immediately try to \Ndepend on someone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.04,0:11:08.87,Dangers_11:02,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(335,1)}Dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.85,0:11:11.37,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Connections between people are a narcotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.87,0:11:10.60,Communication_11:08,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(507,1)}Communication
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.57,0:11:13.09,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Before you know it, you get hooked...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.09,0:11:16.65,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,When I was dealing with the election, \NKomachi gave me my reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.65,0:11:20.07,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,"It's for Komachi." I used that \Nas a front to take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.07,0:11:22.61,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, if I hadn't done that, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.93,0:11:26.80,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I was probably wrong then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.80,0:11:28.09,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,And now, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.09,0:11:29.78,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,The answer I found for myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.78,0:11:31.56,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I have to act for my own reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.56,0:11:36.34,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't I want to let Yukinoshita \Nor Yuigahama become president?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.79,0:11:41.34,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,My true reason for acting, \Nafter getting a reason from someone else...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.47,0:11:52.39,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Because there was something I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.13,0:11:58.86,high_11:56,Text,0000,0000,0000,,High
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.77,0:12:20.88,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.80,0:12:35.09,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Hikki...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.72,0:12:38.32,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,What's up? Why did you knock?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.55,0:12:41.90,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that you didn't have to \Nforce yourself to attend anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.52,0:12:44.13,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I had business here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.83,0:12:46.74,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,W-Want to sit down?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.51,0:13:08.03,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.03,0:13:10.26,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,You're not acting like usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.85,0:13:17.40,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make a request.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.14,0:13:22.21,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Hikki... You're going to talk to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.40,0:13:26.12,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's about the Christmas \Nevent Isshiki brought up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.65,0:13:28.91,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's going a lot worse than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.63,0:13:31.55,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.19,0:13:33.08,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:35.04,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, I know what you want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.43,0:13:37.31,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I took this on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.31,0:13:39.54,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,And I said our helping wouldn't help Isshiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.06,0:13:42.63,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm the one who pushed \NIsshiki to become president.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.30,0:13:45.51,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the kids from Chiba Village?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.51,0:13:48.18,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,The girl from there is helping, \Nbut she's the same as back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.50,0:13:50.64,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.... Rumi-chan, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.64,0:13:52.44,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I want to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.78,0:13:55.68,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,My own actions are the underlying cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:57.87,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm being selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:14:00.56,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But still, I want to ask for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.01,0:14:07.07,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.03,0:14:10.27,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you're saying, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.37,0:14:13.08,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I can't deny that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.92,0:14:15.83,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.78,0:14:24.30,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,If you caused these problems yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.06,0:14:27.36,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,then I think you should solve them yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.67,0:14:33.58,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:37.06,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Forget I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.85,0:14:38.94,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:40.57,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.57,0:14:42.32,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Why does it have to be like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.32,0:14:43.76,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.76,0:14:45.74,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, it is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.10,0:14:47.81,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I should take care of my own problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.81,0:14:49.40,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.75,0:14:50.42,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.42,0:14:53.95,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not! What you're both \Nsaying isn't right at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.95,0:14:57.32,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's not just your fault, Hikki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.32,0:15:01.16,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you're the one who came up with \Nthat stuff, and carried it all out...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.16,0:15:03.30,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,But we were wrong, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.30,0:15:04.88,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,We forced it all onto you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.77,0:15:07.52,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:08.63,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,It is true!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.89,0:15:12.27,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just your fault \Nthings ended up this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.64,0:15:15.06,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.85,0:15:22.22,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I think what you said was \Na little unfair, Yukinon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.86,0:15:24.57,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying this now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.56,0:15:27.32,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You're unfair, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.46,0:15:33.32,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on. This isn't what \NI wanted to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.72,0:15:35.95,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinon, you didn't tell us anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.31,0:15:38.71,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,There are things we can't \Nknow if you don't tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.12,0:15:40.76,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't say anything, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.28,0:15:43.33,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You only made conversation \Nto keep up appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:46.59,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,So if that's what you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.27,0:15:50.72,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what both of you wanted, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.11,0:15:54.63,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,...need to say so, or you'll never know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.55,0:16:00.25,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But there are things you can't understand \Neven if you're told, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.25,0:16:01.75,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:06.44,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you'd told me, I probably \Nwouldn't have accepted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:09.00,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I would've thought there \Nwas something behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.41,0:16:11.96,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,some circumstances making you talk that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:13.82,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,even if it was my own selfish idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.72,0:16:17.84,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,But if we'd talked about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.84,0:16:20.62,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,If I had talked to you more... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.62,0:16:22.29,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.10,0:16:27.88,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Saying you'd understand because \Nyou were told is arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.42,0:16:30.54,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ego trip for the person who said it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.99,0:16:32.81,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,or the conceit of the person who was told.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:35.60,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,After things happen, \Nthere's no guarantee everyone will
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.60,0:16:37.24,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,understand if they talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.26,0:16:41.29,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,So what I want isn't words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.59,0:16:48.00,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,But if you don't say anything, \Nwe'll never have any way to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.65,0:16:50.06,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.06,0:16:52.53,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking you'll understand without \Nbeing told anything is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.38,0:16:55.31,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.59,0:17:01.49,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.09,0:17:04.93,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.42,0:17:08.44,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.60,0:17:11.85,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,What I want isn't words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.85,0:17:14.17,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,What I wanted was definitely there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.99,0:17:17.18,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,And it wasn't mutual understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:19.85,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,or to be friends, or to be together,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:21.43,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,or anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.43,0:17:23.49,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.90,0:17:25.55,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I want to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.24,0:17:27.98,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I want to understand. I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:29.66,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I want to feel at ease knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.66,0:17:31.24,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I want peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.24,0:17:33.80,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Because not understanding terrifies me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.80,0:17:37.24,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Saying I want to understand everything \Nis extremely self-righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.24,0:17:39.62,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's a dictatorial and conceited wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:41.66,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's shameless and repulsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:45.00,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm absolutely disgusted \Nat myself for wanting that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.67,0:17:46.97,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But if...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.50,0:17:50.12,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If we feel the same way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:53.55,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If a relationship exists where we can force
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.07,0:17:57.13,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,that ugly self-consciousness upon \Neach other, and accept it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.83,0:18:02.85,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I know there's no way that can happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.28,0:18:06.23,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I realize that's completely out of reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.46,0:18:08.77,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.66,0:18:17.28,Ore_Main,Hachu,0000,0000,0000,,But still, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.11,0:18:20.28,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.50,0:18:24.48,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I want
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.42,0:18:26.84,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,the real thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.45,0:18:35.99,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Hikki...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.03,0:18:39.95,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.82,0:18:49.01,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.17,0:18:52.52,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.14,0:19:01.45,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Hikki!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:02.70,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,We have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:03.99,Ore_Main,Hikki,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.99,0:19:05.49,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,We have to go together!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:07.37,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinon said she doesn't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:09.76,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I think she just doesn't know what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:12.59,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea, either, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.59,0:19:15.54,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't let it end \Nwithout ever knowing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.54,0:19:16.63,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,This is our only chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:19.22,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen Yukinon act like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.59,0:19:22.53,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,So we have to go now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.39,0:19:33.18,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. I can walk myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.54,0:19:35.34,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.11,0:19:37.17,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.96,0:19:45.03,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... um... I wanted to talk to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.26,0:19:48.41,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Iroha-chan. Later, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.76,0:19:51.02,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, there's no meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.02,0:19:52.87,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I came to tell you that... a-and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.87,0:19:53.88,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.34,0:19:55.35,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.35,0:19:57.21,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.60,0:19:59.97,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for Yukinoshita-senpai, \Nshe's on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.37,0:20:02.72,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.77,0:20:24.14,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.71,0:20:27.99,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.99,0:20:35.83,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "the real thing"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.45,0:20:37.82,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:43.84,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinon, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.79,0:20:46.30,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,What's okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.52,0:20:49.56,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really understand, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.49,0:20:52.56,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,So I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.56,0:20:55.31,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,if we talk, we'll understand more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.60,0:20:58.82,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,But we probably won't really \Nunderstand even then, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.33,0:21:02.57,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,And then we'd probably never understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.02,0:21:06.88,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,But, like, we'd understand \Nthat... or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.99,0:21:11.29,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, I guess I really don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.36,0:21:14.33,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.98,0:21:16.22,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.77,0:21:21.59,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like the way things are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.35,0:21:27.34,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you the one crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:33.48,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You really are...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.72,0:21:36.95,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:53.43,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Hikigaya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.22,0:21:55.37,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.59,0:21:59.93,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I accept your request.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.33,0:22:02.27,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.83,0:22:05.04,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.67,0:22:09.68,Ep_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,But Still, Hikigaya Hachiman Is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.04,0:22:08.16,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.23,0:24:09.01,Next_Ep_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,#09 And, Yukinoshita Yukino Is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.01,0:23:42.48,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,This beer is so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.88,0:23:45.15,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I said some uncharacteristically \Nawesome stuff there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.15,0:23:47.57,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Go, me! I'm such a great teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.57,0:23:48.95,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,No... a great woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.95,0:23:51.74,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a great woman, so why \Ncan't I get married?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.74,0:23:53.49,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! The sampler, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.49,0:23:56.24,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,And a husband, while we're \Nat it! Just kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.24,0:23:59.37,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, Christmas already? Makes me sick...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.37,0:24:01.00,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,If only I didn't have to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:04.05,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,If I didn't have to work, \NI could go out for Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.05,0:24:06.31,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! Highball, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.59,0:24:09.01,Ore_Main_Top,Hira,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna get married...
